Community leaders in California spoke out against statewide sanctuary policies during a roundtable with President Trump. They expressed concerns about the safety of their communities and criticized Governor Jerry Brown for prioritizing illegal criminals over the Hispanic community and American citizens. The leaders highlighted the risks posed by sanctuary policies and shared examples of criminal aliens being released instead of being detained and removed from the United States. These incidents included cases of possession of controlled substances, murder, burglary, and attempted murder. The leaders emphasized the need to protect the safety of residents and called for a change in sanctuary policies.